  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "+nep+VsXx65XZIieLwcnRWWfEgo=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Document share in chat\n\n### Build bundle (sender side)\n\n`buildDriveShareBundle(driveId, [docIds])`:\n\n- `reactorClient.get(docId)` for each doc \u2014 **local reactor is source of truth**.\n- `reactorClient.getOperations(...)` includes unflushed outbox ops (so the recipient gets the absolute latest state, not just what's on Swarm).\n- Fallback to Swarm manifest if a doc is not in the local reactor.\n- Preserves `action.context.signer.signatures` verbatim, so authorship stays intact on import.\n\nReturns: `{ documents[], folders, docFolders, preferredEditor }`.\n\n### ACT upload\n\n```\ncreateGrantees([bob.beeNodePubKey])  -> granteeRef, historyRef\nuploadFile(bundle, { act:true, historyRef, skipEncryption:true })\n                                      -> shareRef, actHistoryAddress\n```\n\n### PSS delivery\n\nAttachment payload:\n\n```\n{\n  kind: \"document-share\",\n  driveId, driveName,\n  shareReference, actHistoryAddress,\n  publisherBeeNodePubKey,\n  documents: [{ id, name, documentType }]\n}\n```\n\n### Recipient side\n\nBob receives PSS, `DocumentShareCard` renders, user clicks **Import**, `downloadFile` with ACT params, then `applyDocumentBundle()` materializes the drive, folders, and docs in Bob's reactor with original IDs and signatures intact.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
    }
  },
